# Currency & Pricing

All monetary values use the centralized stack in [`src/utils/currency.ts`](src/utils/currency.ts), [`src/hooks/useCurrency.ts`](src/hooks/useCurrency.ts), and [`src/components/common/Price.tsx`](src/components/common/Price.tsx). Locale and currency come from [`src/store/settingsStore.ts`](src/store/settingsStore.ts) via `useCurrency` — never read the settings store directly for display.

## Minor Units Only

Store and pass amounts as **integers in minor units** (paise/cents). Use field names `priceCents`, `amountCents`, or prop `amountMinor`.

- Never store display strings (`"$42.00"`, `"₹42"`) or major-unit floats (`42.0`) in mocks, stores, or API types.
- Example: Quiff = `priceCents: 4200` → displays as ₹42.00.

## Display — Component vs Hook

| Context | Use | Import |
|---------|-----|--------|
| Rendered price in JSX | `<Price amountMinor={…} />` | `@/components/common` |
| Button label, template string, non-`Text` UI | `const { format } = useCurrency()` | `@/hooks/useCurrency` |
| Unit tests for formatting | `formatCurrency` from util | `@/utils/currency` |

**Forbidden in components/screens:** hardcoded `$`, `₹`, `€`, `£`; manual `toFixed(2)`; calling `formatCurrency` or `useSettingsStore` for display.

## `Price` Component

- Required prop: `amountMinor` (not `price`, not `amount`).
- Optional: `variant`, `color`, `currency` override, `prefix`.
- Default styling: amber accent via theme — override `color` only when design requires (e.g. primary text in breakdown rows).
- Use `prefix` only for semantic modifiers (`"-"` for discounts). **Do not** use `prefix="+ "` for add-on pricing; show full service price via `priceCents`.

## Hooks & Aggregation

- Hooks sum cents, then format: `format(sumVariantPrices(ids))` or `format(computeTotalCents(items))`.
- Expose **numbers** (`estimateCents`, `totalCents`) from hooks; let components call `Price` or `format`.
- Single source of truth per item: use `priceCents` (full price), not separate add-on fields.

## Mock & Data Layer

- Mock interfaces use `priceCents` / `amountCents` (see [`serviceVariantMock.ts`](src/data/serviceVariantMock.ts), [`paymentSummaryMock.ts`](src/data/paymentSummaryMock.ts)).
- Provide small pure helpers (`sumVariantPrices`, `computeTotalCents`) in data modules — hooks import them; components do not.

## Settings Store Boundary

- Components and screens **must not** read `useSettingsStore` for formatting — use `useCurrency()` or `<Price />`.
- Only settings UI or app bootstrap may call `setCurrency` / `setLocale`.

## Examples

```tsx
// BAD — hardcoded symbol
<Text>₹42.00</Text>

// GOOD
<Price amountMinor={4200} />
```

```tsx
// BAD — hardcoded symbol in CTA
<Button title={`Book Now - ₹${total}`} />

// GOOD — hook builds label
const { format } = useCurrency();
const label = `Book Now - ${format(totalCents)}`;
```

```tsx
// BAD — add-on field and + prefix
addOnPriceCents: 600
<Price amountMinor={addOnPriceCents} prefix="+ " />

// GOOD — full price everywhere
priceCents: 4200
<Price amountMinor={priceCents} />
```
